<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ullrich Keeps Tour of Spain Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AVILA, Spain (AP) -- Frank Vandenbroucke of Belgium won the 19th  
stage of the Tour of Spain cycling race Friday, and German Jan 
Ullrich kept his overall lead with two days left. 
</P>
<P>
	Ullrich ended the leg as he began it, with a 31-second lead over  
his nearest rival Igor Gonzalez Galdeano of Spain. 
</P>
<P>
	Vandenbroucke covered Friday's 114-miles from El Escorial to  
Avila in west-central Spain in 4 hours, 54 minutes and 18 seconds. 
The group of cyclists that included Ullrich and Gonzalez Galdeano 
were 20 seconds back. 
</P>
<P>
	The Spaniard said catching Ullrich would require the German to  
make an uncharacteristic mistake in Saturday's sage -- a 2.8-mile 
time-trial. 
</P>
<P>
	``If Ullrich slips up, we will try to take advantage, but it  
isn't going to be easy,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The race ends Sunday in Madrid.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
