<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Friday, Sept. 24, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Stocks End Down; Dow Off 39.26  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rounded out a dismal week with a volatile  
session but generally modest losses today. Investors continued 
selling semiconductor and major computer stocks, but made some 
cautious overtures toward battered shares of Internet and financial 
companies. The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 39.26 at 
10,279.33. The Dow finished the week 524.30 points below last 
Friday's close, a loss of 4.9 percent. Broader stock indicators 
were also down. The Nasdaq composite index with its many tech 
stocks fell 9.42 to 2,740.41. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
