<HEADLINE> Russia Awaits Oct. IMF Loan Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- The Russian government expects to receive the next  
$640 million installment of a $4.5 billion loan package from the 
International Monetary Fund in October, a top official said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``There is a possibility that a decision involving the tranche  
will be made by mid-October,'' First Deputy Prime Minister Viktor 
Khristenko said. That would mean the loan would be received at the 
end of that month. 
</P>
<P>
	Khristenko said an audit of the Russian central bank's  
transactions through offshore subsidiaries has not come up with 
evidence of wrongdoing by the bank or the government. The audit is 
expected to be completed soon. 
</P>
<P>
	``Reviews of all accounts have not brought up any claims,'' he  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The IMF has come under fire after an alleged money-laundering  
scheme involving Russians and the Bank of New York. No one has been 
charged in the case, but the IMF is considering whether it should 
impose additional controls on the use of IMF funds in Russia. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
