<HEADLINE> Boy Arrested After Infant's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LYNN, Mass. (AP) -- A 10-year-old boy pleaded innocent to a  
juvenile charge of murder Friday in the death of his 5-week-old 
relative whose body was found stuffed in a knapsack in a bedroom 
closet. 
</P>
<P>
	Police arrested the boy, who was not identified because of his  
age, after finding the infant boy's body in the house where the two 
lived, prosecutors said. Authorities did not say how the two were 
related or what led them to the young suspect. 
</P>
<P>
	There was ``significant evidence of trauma'' to the infant,  
Essex County District Attorney Kevin Burke said without 
elaborating. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of death had not been determined, prosecutors said. An  
autopsy was scheduled for Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Etoya Vaughn, 22, called authorities to her home about 3:45 a.m.  
Friday, saying she could not find her son, Davion, police said. 
After finding no signs of forced entry to the home, officers went 
inside and found the body. 
</P>
<P>
	The suspect was ordered held for 20 days and is scheduled to  
re-appear in juvenile court on Oct. 14. If convicted, he could be 
committed to the Department of Youth Services until the age of 18, 
Burke said. 
  	   	
