Penny Pollack, dining editor at Chicago Magazine. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think there is ever a reason to go back unless you had  
an out-of-town guest who really needed to go there,'' Pollack said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lunchtime customers had mixed opinions Thursday.  
</P>
<P>
	``I love the Cubs and Sammy, but Michael's an icon in this  
city,'' said former Chicagoan Scott Neururer, 38, who was visiting 
from Los Angeles with his wife and baby. ``It's sad to see anything 
(related to) Michael go away.'' 
</P>
