<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pan American Hires New Hoops Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- Bob Hoffman, men's basketball coach at  
Oklahoma Baptist for nine seasons, was hired Friday as coach of the 
Texas-Pan American basketball program. 
</P>
<P>
	Hoffman inherits a program that has lost and regained its NCAA  
certification, been dropped by its athletic conference and dealt 
with alleged misuse of university money by previous coach Delray 
Brooks -- all in the past three years. 
</P>
<P>
	Hoffman said during a news conference Friday that he would work  
on restoring the Broncs' reputation by ``just doing the right thing 
and doing it as often as we can.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``We're in this thing together,'' Hoffman said. ``We're going to  
be about servant leadership, not power leadership.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hoffman had a 242-79 record at Oklahoma Baptist, making it to  
the NAIA championship game in 1993 and 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Bison teams went to five consecutive NAIA tournaments this  
decade. After missing the tournament in 1998, they made it to the 
1999 NAIA quarterfinals and finished last season 31-7. Hoffman was 
Sooner Athletic Conference coach of the year in 1996 and 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Hoffman previously coached the Southern Nazarene women's team,  
which won the 1989 NAIA championship. 
</P>
<P>
	``We accept coach Hoffman's resignation with sincere regret, but  
he will go with our very best wishes,'' Oklahoma Baptist president 
Mark Brister said in a statement released Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Brooks was fired on Aug. 23 because Texas-Pan American officials  
believe he deposited a $25,000 check from Southwest Missouri into 
his personal account and then made withdrawals from the account. 
</P>
<P>
	Brooks acknowledged that $25,000 was placed in his account last  
December but denied that he deposited it or that he told someone 
else to do so. 
</P>
<P>
	Hidalgo County District Attorney Rene Guerra has said he will  
seek a grand jury indictment of Brooks. 
</P>
<P>
	Texas-Pan Am athletic director William Weidner said Hoffman's  
reputation was important. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were looking for someone who had unquestioned integrity,  
someone who truly cares about the student athlete as a person, not 
just as a basketball player, and has demonstrated that through the 
years through actions,'' Weidner said. 
</P>
<P>
	Brooks played at Indiana and Providence and most recently spent  
five years as an assistant at Kentucky. 
</P>
<P>
	He was hired to restore Pan American's reputation, sullied when  
the school lost its NCAA certification in July 1996 over charges 
that two assistants improperly helped potential recruits with 
correspondence coursework. 
</P>
<P>
	Certification was restored in May 1998, after the Sun Belt  
Conference had dropped the school. Texas-Pan American remains an 
independent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
