<HEADLINE> Bob Barker To Leave Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Less than a week after surgery to clear a  
blocked artery, game show host Bob Barker plans to go home to 
California, his publicist said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Barker was scheduled to check out of George Washington  
University Hospital on Saturday, Henri Bollinger said in a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Barker underwent surgery on Monday to clear an artery in his  
neck that was impeding the flow of blood to his brain. He was 
admitted Sept. 16 to the hospital for fatigue. Tests later revealed 
his left carotid artery was 85 percent blocked. 
</P>
<P>
	``Mr. Barker is experiencing a good recovery from surgery and  
will now need to go home and rest,'' his neurosurgeon, Anthony 
Caputy, said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	A longtime animal rights activist, Barker, 75, was in Washington  
to lobby for a bill that would ban circuses from using elephants. 
</P>
<P>
	His illness is not expected to interfere with production of  
``The Price Is Right'' because the show is taped well in advance. 
Barker has been host of the program since 1972. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
