<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> New Ads Aren't What You Think </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- All over town, people are doing double and  
triple takes at the new ad campaign featuring the initials for the 
clothing company French Connection U.K. 
</P>
<P>
	The ads, prominently displayed atop many New York City cabs,  
also show models posed alongside risque text. ``Think my clothes 
off,'' says one. ``Wash your mind out,'' says an ad in the 
company's SoHo store. 
</P>
<P>
	But not everybody finds it clever. Even New York's notoriously  
gruff taxi drivers have complained about the way the initials, 
fcuk, easily can be misread as bad language. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's clearly denigrating to the industry,'' said Taxi  
Commissioner Allan J. Fromberg, who sent a letter to the 
London-based company asking it to change the approach. 
</P>
<P>
	The London public relations office for French Connection did not  
return a call for comment, and the company that designed the 
campaign is not discussing the ads. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
