<DOCNO> APW19990924.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-24 07:00:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> LVMH Adds Tailored Shirts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- France's LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton has  
acquired a majority stake in the British company Thomas Pink, 
adding tailored shirts to its growing portfolio of luxury goods. 
</P>
<P>
	LVMH did not disclose details of the purchase announced Friday,  
but the company said it would expand Thomas Pink's presence in the 
United States and Europe. 
</P>
<P>
	``We plan to accelerate the development of Thomas Pink and are  
very happy to work with the management team which will stay in 
place,'' Louis Vuitton Capital Chairman Daniel Piette said in a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas Pink has a chain of 20 shops, 13 in London including  
flagship stores in fashionable Jermyn Street and Sloane street, as 
well as a recently opened store in New York. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
