<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-24 21:40:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Fan Attacks Astros' Spiers on Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- A fan came on to the field and attacked Houston  
Astros right fielder Bill Spiers in the sixth inning of Friday 
night's game against the Milwaukee Brewers. 
</P>
<P>
	As the Brewers came to bat, the spectator jumped Spiers from  
behind and knocked him to the ground. 
</P>
<P>
	Spiers left an inning later with whiplash. He is listed as  
day-to-day. 
</P>
<P>
	The entire Astros bench came to Spiers defense. Mike Hampton,  
the starting pitcher, raced out and pummeled the spectator as other 
teammates tried to separate Hampton from the attacker. Astros 
relievers jumped over the bullpen wall in center field and joined 
the melee. 
</P>
<P>
	Spiers left momentarily with a welt under his left eye and a  
bloody nose. He stayed in for the rest of the inning, but was then 
removed. 
</P>
<P>
	The unidentified attacker, 23, from South Beloit, Ill., was  
handcuffed and led off the field by Milwaukee County sheriff's 
deputies. The sheriff's office said there would be no official 
identification of him unless charges are filed. 
</P>
<P>
	He will be formally charged Monday, a Brewers spokesman said.  
The spectator faces two counts of battery -- one for attacking 
Spiers, the other for slugging a ground crew member who was 
defending the pitcher -- and one count of disorderly conduct. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
