<HEADLINE> O'Neill Named Publisher of E&AMP;P </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Dennis O'Neill, formerly vice president of sales  
and advertising for Editor &AMP; Publisher Co., has been named vice 
president and publisher, company officials announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Neill's promotion follows the recent acquisition of The Editor  
&AMP; Publisher Co. by BPI Communications. 
</P>
<P>
	In his new post, O'Neill will oversee management of the weekly  
flagship Editor &AMP; Publisher magazine, the monthly Free Paper 
Publisher, the online magazine MediaINFO.com, as well as the 
company's directories, conferences, and electronic publishing 
businesses. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Neill, 42, joined Editor &AMP; Publisher in 1995 as head of the  
newly formed New Media Division. He was promoted to vice president 
for sales and advertising in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Previously, O'Neill was president and CEO of TV Update Inc.  
</P>
<P>
	BPI publishes 23 magazines including Adweek, Brandweek,  
Mediaweek, MC, Billboard, Shoot, The Hollywood Reporter, 
Architecture, Interiors and American Artist. 
</P>
</TEXT>
