<HEADLINE> How Earnings Affect Social Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	New Social Security statements coming to workers this year  
highlight how benefits vary depending on a person's earnings. 
According the Social Security Administration, a 40-year-old 
worker's earnings would affect benefits as follows, assuming he or 
she continued at about the same salary until retirement, disability 
or death. 

1998 Earnings:                           $13,002    $28,894   $68,400
Monthly Retirement Benefits:                $577       $953    $1,373
Monthly Disability Benefits:                $622     $1,025    $1,587
Maximum Survivors Benefits:                 $934     $1,873    $2,879
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
