<HEADLINE> Clerk Strike Closes Belgian Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) -- A nationwide strike by clerks demanding  
better working conditions closed many banks today in Belgium. 
</P>
<P>
	Unions said they are worried that Saturday shifts will become  
more widespread and that consolidation in the sector will lead to 
dismissals and less-flexible working conditions. 
</P>
<P>
	The Belgian Bankers' Association has been meeting with the  
Christian Democrat and Socialist unions throughout the summer but 
have failed to come to an agreement. 
  	   	
</P>
