<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Train Crewmen Honored for Heroism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Two Canadian men who helped pull a fellow  
crewman from a wrecked locomotive after a train derailment were 
among 22 people honored for acts of heroism by the Carnegie Hero 
Fund Commission. 
</P>
<P>
	Joseph Moloney and Kerry Osborne pulled Donald Collings from the  
CP Rail locomotive, which derailed during a storm, then stayed with 
him for over two hours until rescue crews arrived. 
</P>
<P>
	Collings suffered a head injury and damage to his heart, but  
lived through the ordeal on April 7, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Recipients of the Carnegie Medal for heroism, which also  
includes a $3,000 award, were being honored Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The commission was founded in 1904 by steel magnate Andrew  
Carnegie after he was inspired by rescue tales following a mine 
disaster. It has honored over 8,300 people since then. 
</P>
<P>
	Also named Friday were:  
</P>
<P>
	--Nelson W. Baker Jr., 27, of Patton, Pa. He drowned Dec. 19  
while trying to save a 14-year-old boy whose bike had fallen into a 
frozen creek. 
</P>
<P>
	--Frank B, Boeger, 67, of Sterling Heights, Mich. He died Aug.  
15, 1998, while trying to save a 9-year-old girl in Lake Michigan. 
Someone else saved the girl. 
</P>
<P>
	--Burnell Gilleland, 70, of Haskell, Texas. He and 23-year-old  
Walter McMeans suffocated Aug. 3, 1997, when Gilleland tried to 
save McMeans in a gas well. 
</P>
<P>
	--Gerald D. Lloyd, 45, of Salinas, Calif. He died June 9, 1997,  
while trying to rescue an employee after a man opened fire on 
workers at the Monterey Presidio Logistical Support Center. 
</P>
<P>
	--Keith L. Putnam, 15, of Hanahan, S.C. He died Aug. 6, 1998,  
while saving a 21-year-old from an oncoming train. 
</P>
<P>
	--Christopher A.P. Smith, 19, of Ontario, Canada. He drowned June  
16, 1998, while trying to save Jeffrey Brasser, who also drowned, 
in Lake Erie. 
</P>
<P>
	--Robert J. Ballentine, 36, of Claymont, Del. The pastor  
intervened to disarm a suspect during a police chase at a 
convenience store on Oct. 30, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	--Odette Tremblay, 41, of Quebec, Canada. She saved a 49-year-old  
man from a burning car on March 5, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	--Jessica R. Richardson, 44, of Belleville, Ill. She saved a  
7-year-old boy from a pit bull on March 27, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	--Daryl Elder, 35, of Titusville, Fla. He saved a 50-year-old man  
from a canal after a car wreck on April 16, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	--Jerald Bowman, 30, of Cocoa, Fla. He helped Elder in the rescue  
of the man from the car wreck. 
</P>
<P>
	--Barry Pitt, 37, of Draffenville, Ky. He saved a 69-year-old man  
from a burning mobile home on May 5, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	--James A. Shannon, 28, of Plymouth, Mass. He saved an  
83-year-old man from a burning house on May 17, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	--Robert D. DeLargy, 35, of Bonne Terre, Mo. He saved a  
7-year-old from a burning car on Nov. 24, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	--David Hammond, 51, of Bonne Terre, Mo. He helped DeLargy with  
the rescue of the 7-year-old. 
</P>
<P>
	--Gregory Gobble, 30, of Kirkwood, Mo. He pulled a woman and her  
daughter out of a burning car after a head-on collision on June 17, 
1998. 
</P>
<P>
	--Richard Gibson, 39, of Acton, Calif. The highway patrolman  
pushed a man out of the path of an oncoming car on an interstate 
highway in California on Nov. 10, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	--Leslie M. Hough, 31, of Coram, N.Y., who pulled a 43-year-old  
woman out of a burning pickup truck on June 10, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	--Thomas S. McKeough, 41, of Hastings, Mich. He saved a couple  
from a car that went into an icy pond on Dec. 22, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	--Richard T. Baker, 36, of Coopersville, Mich. He helped McKeough  
in the rescue of the couple from the icy pond. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
