<HEADLINE> House Roll Call on Gun Control Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The 305-117 roll call Thursday by which the House urged  
negotiators for a House-Senate conference on a juvenile justice 
bill to include language closing loopholes on criminals buying 
guns. 
</P>
<P>
	A ``yes'' vote is a vote to approve the motion.  
</P>
<P>
	Voting yes were 174 Democrats, 130 Republicans and one  
independent. 
</P>
