<HEADLINE> Timken Explores Options for Latrobe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CANTON, Ohio (AP) -- Timken Co. is looking at alternatives for  
its Latrobe Steel subsidiary, including a possible acquisition or 
strategic alliance. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said it has hired J.P. Morgan &AMP; Co. to help  
determine a strategy to keep Latrobe competitive. 
</P>
<P>
	Latrobe Steel, based in Latrobe, Pa., makes and sells specialty  
steels. Timken acquired it in 1975. It represents about 20 percent 
of Timken's steel business. 
</P>
<P>
	W.R. Timken Jr., Timken chairman, said the company also is  
seeking opportunities in the bearing and alloy steel businesses. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
