<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Demographic Shift Hurts GOP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- For the first time in 15 years, Republicans  
account for fewer than half of Orange County's registered voters. 
</P>
<P>
	In the county that proudly proclaimed itself ``Reagan Country''  
and was a crucial GOP campaign stop, only 49.98 percent of the 
registered voters are Republicans, according to a Sept. 18 count. 
</P>
<P>
	The last time Republicans made up less than half of the county's  
voting bloc was during the 1984 primary. 
</P>
<P>
	Once a mainly conservative white bastion, the county has changed  
demographically. Hispanics comprise a large and growing segment of 
the population, and have tended overwhelmingly to register as 
Democrats. Thirty-two percent of the county's registered voters are 
Democrats. 
</P>
<P>
	The ranks of independents and third-party voters also are  
growing. According to the latest count, 18 percent registered with 
third parties or declined to state their affiliation. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
