<DOCNO> APW19990924.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-24 08:30:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jags' McManus Likely Out for Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Jacksonville Jaguars middle linebacker  
Tom McManus will have surgery on a torn tendon in his right foot 
and is expected to be out for the rest of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	The fifth-year veteran was hurt last week on Carolina's failed  
2-point conversion attempt at the end of Jacksonville's 22-20 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
	The surgery will be done sometime in the next two weeks. McManus  
is expected to be placed on injured reserve in the next few days. 
If he is, he'll be lost for the season. 
</P>
<P>
	``It burns me out,'' McManus told The Florida Times-Union. ``I  
finally win the job, and then this happens. I was just starting to 
feel comfortable, starting to feel like everything was clicking.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McManus beat out Bryan Schwartz for the starting job in  
preseason. Coach Tom Coughlin said either Schwartz or Lonnie Marts 
will start in McManus' spot Sunday when the Jaguars play the 
Tennessee Titans. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
