<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Higer, Tokyo Stocks Plunge / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The U.S. dollar gained against the yen today on  
uncertainty about Japan's economic recovery. Tokyo share prices 
fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 104.42 yen as of late today, up 0.14 yen from  
its level late Wednesday and also higher than its late New York 
level of 103.95 yen overnight. It ranged during the day from 103.72 
yen to 105.15 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Japanese markets were closed Thursday for a national holiday.  
</P>
<P>
	Broad selling on the Tokyo Stock Exchange was also seen as  
behind the dollar's gain. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average dropped 454.03  
points, or 2.62 percent, to finish at 16,871.73. 
</P>
<P>
	On Wednesday, the average closed down 607.03 points, or 3.39  
percent, its biggest one-day loss since Oct. 8, 1998, when the 
index fell 799.55 points to close at 13,026.06. 
</P>
<P>
	``The plunge of the Nikkei has invoked fears for Japan's  
economic recovery in overseas investors' minds,'' said Ryuichi 
Takami, vice president of foreign exchange at Sanwa Bank. 
</P>
<P>
	``They rushed in to buy dollars to make up for their  
dollar-short positions.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Some traders continued to anticipate a possible announcement of  
coordinated action by Japan and other Group of Seven industrialized 
nations to weaken the surging yen at a meeting in Washington this 
weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	Share prices fell following an overnight drop on Wall Street.  
The Dow Jones industrial average dropped 205.48 points, or 2.0 
percent, to close at 10,318.59. 
</P>
<P>
	``Uncertainty over the macroeconomic environment has caused the  
stock sell-off,'' said Yuichi Kohashi, chief strategist at Daiwa 
Securities. 
</P>
<P>
	The rise of the yen in recent months has set off fears that it  
may choke off Japan's fragile economic recovery. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was down 48.86 points, or 3.3 percent, to 1,430.42. 
The TOPIX closed down 50.05 points, or 3.27 percent, on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Volume on the first section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange was  
estimated at 640.3 million shares, up from 590.6 million shares 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Decliners overwhelmed advancers 1,053 to 207, while 78 issues  
were unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 109.55 yen at  
midafternoon, down slightly from 109.57 yen late Wednesday in 
Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark Japanese government bond fell to  
1.7100 percent from Wednesday's finish of 1.7950 percent. Its price 
rose 0.73 points to 99.91. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
