<HEADLINE> Rite Aid To Cut 330 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAMP HILL, Pa. (AP) -- Rite Aid Corp. is eliminating 330  
positions to cut costs by $31.5 million a year. 
</P>
<P>
	The job cuts announced Friday involve corporate and field  
staff-support positions for the Camp Hill-based Rite Aid, which 
operates more than 4,000 stores in 30 states. Rite Aid has more 
than 85,000 employees overall. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement came a day after the company said it would  
close its Ogden, Utah, distribution center next year, cutting about 
500 jobs. The company said it was shifting its West Coast 
distribution network to a new facility in Lancaster, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
	Rite Aid has had a disappointing financial performance in the  
past year. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
