	Halper, a minority owner of the Yankees, began his collection  
simply with player autographs. It just grew from there. 
</P>
<P>
	Goodwillie, who spent two years after college playing Class A  
baseball at Newark, Ohio, said, ``Barry never asked me for my 
autograph.'' 



  	   	
</P>
