<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Raiders' Stinchcomb Out for Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ALAMEDA, Calif. (AP) -- Offensive tackle Matt Stinchcomb, the  
Oakland Raiders' first-round draft pick this year, will have 
surgery on his separated left shoulder and miss his entire rookie 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Stinchcomb, who has been out since preseason, will have surgery  
within the next few days. 
</P>
<P>
	``We hung in there for a long time, Matt did and our staff did,  
trying to get as many opinions and as much research as we did 
before we made this decision,'' Raiders coach Jon Gruden said. 
``He's a bright young prospect. It's a disappointment to him and 
it's a disappointment to our squad.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Stinchcomb, who also had a problem with the shoulder at Georgia,  
was injured during training camp and aggravated the shoulder during 
an Aug. 31 preseason game against the San Francisco 49ers. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
