<HEADLINE> Wrestler Charged With Reckless Act </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Jerry Lawler, pro wrestler and candidate  
for mayor, was indicted Thursday on charges of running over an 
airport officer's foot after she wrote him a parking ticket. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawler was charged with reckless endangerment, punishable by up  
to two years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Officer Camille Pegues said she ticketed Lawler's vehicle in  
March because it was left unattended in a no-parking zone. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawler said the officer was nowhere near his van when he drove  
off. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawler is one of 15 candidates in the Oct. 7 race for mayor.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
